Program: The History Hour
Title: How I Survived a Fire on a Plane
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswqm0
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 16 Sep 2018
A lucky escape from a jet plane fire in the 1970s, Chamberlain's talks with Hitler in 1938 plus the killing of the South African anti-apartheid campaigner, Steve Biko. Also toxic waste being shipped around the world in the 1980s and how Britain became obsessed with the idea that aliens were responsible for crop circles. (Photo: Ricardo Trajano as a young man. Copyright: Ricardo Trajano) Show less